@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_axis_falsifier_coverage_rationale_13 = Single falsifier misses the form; three orthogonal gates (cut + season + image) capture the device-density a 2-line haiku must hit to compensate for the lost line. :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
  => rationale of axis axis_falsifier_coverage
  |> kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices (auto-ingested Пү-cycle)

@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_axis_phonological_density_name_14 = Phonological density: per-line sonic-device load when the line budget shrinks :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
  => name of axis axis_phonological_density
  |> kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices (auto-ingested Пү-cycle)

@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_axis_phonological_density_rationale_15 = If 2-line form must carry the same sonic weight as 3-line, devices must densify per line. Alliteration on the kireji-cut consonants and internal assonance across the cut are the cheapest densifiers. :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
  => rationale of axis axis_phonological_density
  |> kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices (auto-ingested Пү-cycle)

@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_axis_imagery_juxtaposition_name_16 = Imagery juxtaposition: diptych vs single-image schema across the kireji cut :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
  => name of axis axis_imagery_juxtaposition
  |> kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices (auto-ingested Пү-cycle)

@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_axis_imagery_juxtaposition_rationale_17 = The kireji cut is the haiku's primary semantic engine. In 2-line form the cut becomes more salient (only one cut available), so the diptych schema is forced rather than chosen. :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
  => rationale of axis axis_imagery_juxtaposition
  |> kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices (auto-ingested Пү-cycle)

@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_tier1_kireji_internal_cut_rationale_18 = In a 2-line haiku, kireji must land at the line break (only cut available). The cutting word's sole job is to force juxtaposition between line-A and line-B. Without it, the form degenerates to a couplвҖҰ :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
  => rationale of axis tier1_kireji_internal_cut
  |> kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices (auto-ingested Пү-cycle)

@C kick_bench_smoke_2_line_haiku_poetic_devices_tier1_kigo_compression_rationale_19 = Without a kigo, the form is senryЕ« not haiku. Under 2-line constraint the kigo must be folded into one of the two images (cannot afford a separate kigo line). Compression forces dual-purpose words: iвҖҰ :: omega_cycle_kick-bench-smoke-2-line-haiku-poetic-devices [7]
